@mookiemorjax birds are not directly generating their energy from flight - in fact they burn a massive amount of energy flying. They use flight to get food, but that’s not nearly the same as photosynthesis…

But you have a very good point about wind getting its energy from the sun…

Still… it’s surprising to me that nature hasn’t evolved some creature that gets its energy *directly* from some kind of mechanical process like wind.
